.TH "snd_hda_mixer_amp_volume_get" 9 "snd_hda_mixer_amp_volume_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hda_mixer_amp_volume_get \- Get callback for a standard AMP mixer volume
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hda_mixer_amp_volume_get
.BI "(struct snd_kcontrol *kcontrol "  ","
.BI "struct snd_ctl_elem_value *ucontrol "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kcontrol" 12
ctl element
.IP "ucontrol" 12
pointer to get/store the data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The control element is supposed to have the private_value field
set up via HDA_COMPOSE_AMP_VAL*() or related macros.
